Sally McCluskey ( b. in Omaha , Nebraska ) is an American writer of romance novels as Bethany Campbell and Lisa Harris . Sally McCluskey was born and raised in Nebraska . She attended Northern Illinois University , where she met her future husband , Dan McCluskey , a fellow student . After graduation McCluskey , who majored in English and minored in art , worked on a freelance basis as a writer for several greeting card companies . She sold her first romance novel in 1984 . She has has won three Romance Writers of America RITA Awards , three Romantic Times Reviewer Awards , a Maggie Award , and the Daphne du Maurier Award of Excellence . Romance Writers of America . 